preds: ['This hotel is located in the heart of San Francisco, steps from Union Square and the Embarcadero.', 'The hotel offers many different rides each day- slow flat, fast flat, slow mountain, fast mountain, 1/2 day, full day.', 'The hotel has a limited number of connecting rooms.', 'This hotel is my favorite hotel. Everyone from housekeeping to front desk staff to valets. Turn-down service is Sucre chocolates on your pillow. Sweets for the sweet dreams.', 'This hotel is fantastic. They shipped it to me intact and untouched, cash and all! Glad to see good people and they are definitely the staff there. Staff were all nice and friendly. Parking was free, and if you’re Hilton Honors, you get a free gift at check in.', '', 'This hotel is also absurd for St. Louis.', 'The hotel is located in the French Quarter, close to Bourbon Street.', "The hotel is spectacular. Like stepping into the 1800s, except for all the modern accomodations (AC, etc). Linda, the owner is a sweetheart. She's a wonderful and kind person with a whole lot of patience for a 16 month old that thinks every sphere shaped object is a bouncy ball. Every morning the chef waited for us to come downstairs before putting out some delicious, authentic Louisiana food. Seriously...it was exceptional. More of awesome treatment...skipping the end. Linda, shipped the items to us out of her own pocket...!!!!!! WHAT?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!?!", '', 'This hotel features complimentary breakfast.', '', 'This hotel is some of the oldest, most dilapidated properties in the hotel business. labels: [["The hotel has a dock and hammocks. They had a photo booth and Valentine's candy for Valentine's Day evening."], ['The hotel offers binoculars for bird watching. They have bike rentals and a 360 degree view of Santa Barbara. They are in close proximity to all the major attractions, located across from Saks, and half a block from State St.'], ['The hotel had events. They had face painters and Santa clause.'], [''], ['The hotel has amenities that include put put golf, oversized chess set, paddle boat, touch tank, konk children center, pet play zone, pirate island, water slide, shark riding, surfboard riding, beach access, beach volleyball, tennis court, water sports. They also have live music.'], ['Less then a two minute drive or five minute walk to Wawa, there is also a bowling alley, hair salon, and trampoline park within the same parking lot.'], [''], [''], ['The hotel is in close proximity to the Pacific Ocean and has a VIP entrance to Coral. They offer Pacific views. Customers can grab a complimentary surfboard and use a private access gate to access Butterfly Beach.'], ["It is a five minute walk from the hotel to a nice beach where you can rent boards or skate down the path. Customers drove down to State street for drinks and apps, foot massages and Salt Cave. A customer's room had a Buddhist book."], ['The hotel has bike rentals. They have guitars, keyboards and even a banjo. The hotel is close to a 24 hr bar, the St Charles street car which goes right into the heart of the Garden District and beyond.'], ['The hotel has a boutique by the lobby with unique stuff.'], ['The hotel has nightlife. On a Thursday night, they had an outside stage with live music of mostly country and right near beach access with a bar and deck. They also have a proper nightclub that plays hip-hop and an electronic music.'], ["The hotel is in a historic building. It's only a block away from the bus station and only a couple blocks from the main casinos. A customer attended several poetry readings, parties, a folk festival, and an art show at the hotel."], ['']]

labels: [["The hotel building location allows you to access John's Village and all it's attractions by walking under the bridge over John's Pass without having to cross the main road. Under the bridge is a local favorite spot to fish. The hotel has beach access."], ["The hote is on the beach. They have a ping pong room. The staff can all dance and sing. They are just 10 minutes North of downtown Santa Barbara. They are a few blocks to Isla Vista with coffee at Caje, nachos at Freebirds and pizza from Woodstock. And you can have late night fun at Dublin's and Sam's. They hosted activities including Family Carnival with 3 legged races, a pie-eating contest, a water balloon contest, and temporary tattoos. They also had hula hoop and limbo contests, and hermit crab races. They had Casino Night where customers can do gambling with play money and dancing. They had a Campfire sing-along, Karaoke night and the Farewell show where they showed a video montage of pictures from the week. Other daytime activities included tennis, yoga, golf, wine country tours, softball game with staff vs. the vacationers. Customers can hire a babysitter."], ["They have a copy of Alice's Adventure in Wonderland as a substitute. Canal street is only 2 blocks away and the trolley line is right there. The hotel is an easy walk to Harrah's casino, the river, and the French Quarter. There is a breakfast/brunch place across the street, Ruby Slippers."], ['The hotel offers Hiking, Golf. The room offers views of Tucson at night. The hotel is minutes to the 10-fwy and about an hour to Tombstone or Nogales Mexico down the 19-fwy.'], [''], ['The hotel has a river with boat tours in their looby. They have live plants, fountains with colored back lights, trails, koi ponds. They do a Christmas presentation as well.'], ['The hotel is a casino. They have a babysitter for the kids. They have games, and a new game with electric helicopters and remote control cars as prizes.'], [''], ['']]

labels: [["The hotel building location allows you to access John's Village and all it's attractions by walking under the bridge over John's Pass without having to cross the main road. Under the bridge is a local favorite spot to fish. The hotel has beach access."], ["The hote is on the beach. They have a ping pong room. The staff can all dance and sing. They are just 10 minutes North of downtown Santa Barbara. They are a few blocks to Isla Vista with coffee at Caje, nachos at Freebirds and pizza from Woodstock. And you can have late night fun at Dublin's and Sam's. They hosted activities including Family Carnival with 3 legged races, a pie-eating contest, a water balloon contest, and temporary tattoos. They also had hula hoop and limbo contests, and hermit crab races. They had Casino Night where customers can do gambling with play money and dancing. They had a Campfire sing-along, Karaoke night and the Farewell show where they showed a video montage of pictures from the week. Other daytime activities included tennis, yoga, golf, wine country tours, softball game with staff vs. the vacationers. Customers can hire a babysitter."], ["They have a copy of Alice's Adventure in Wonderland as a substitute. It is within walking distance of many attractions (museums, historical sites, restaurants, etc.)"], [''], ['From the hotel, a customer walked to the beach, rented kayaks, and paddled through the mangroves.'], [''], [''], ['Great restaurant choices within walking distance.'], ["The 11 bus on Magazine street, right outside the resort, can take people to the National World War II Museum and to the Audubon Zoo. Canal street is only 2 blocks away and the trolley line is right there. The hotel is an easy walk to Harrah's casino, the river, and the French Quarter. There is a breakfast/brunch place across the street, Ruby Slippers."], ['The hotel offers Hiking, Golf. The room offers views of Tucson at night. The hotel is minutes to the 10-fwy and about an hour to Tombstone or Nogales Mexico down the 19-fwy.'], [''], ['The hotel has a river with boat tours in their looby. They have live plants, fountains with colored back lights, trails, koi ponds. They do a Christmas presentation as well.'], ['The hotel is a casino. They have a babysitter for the kids. They have games, and a new game with electric helicopters and remote control cars as prizes.'], [''], ['']]

labels: [["The hotel building location allows you to access John's Village and all it's attractions by walking under the bridge over John's Pass without having to cross the main road. They are just 10 minutes North of downtown Santa Barbara. They are a few blocks to Isla Vista with coffee at Caje, nachos at Freebirds and pizza from Woodstock. And you can have late night fun at Dublin's and Sam's. They hosted activities including Family Carnival with 3 legged races, a pie-eating contest, a water balloon contest, and temporary tattoos. They also had hula hoop and limbo contests, and hermit crab races. They had Casino Night where customers can do gambling with play money and dancing. They had a Campfire sing-along, Karaoke night and the Farewell show where they showed a video montage of pictures from the week. Other daytime activities included tennis, yoga, golf, wine country tours, softball game with staff vs. the vacationers.
